text="New forester init command">New <fr:code>forester init</fr:code> command</fr:title></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>To make it easier to set up a new forest, we have added a <fr:code>forester init</fr:code> command; when you run this command in an empty directory, it will initialise a git repository with a submodule for the <fr:link
href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/forester-base-theme"
type="external">default theme</fr:link> pinned to the correct release, and a <fr:link
href="foreign-forester-jms-00RG.xml"
title="Forester 4.0 › forest configuration via TOML"
addr="//forester/jms-00RG"
type="local">configuration file</fr:link>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
show-metadata="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="foreign-forester-jonmsterling.xml"
title="Jon Sterling"
addr="//forester/jonmsterling"
type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>6</fr:month><fr:day>15</fr:day></fr:date><fr:anchor>8554</fr:anchor><fr:addr
type="user">//forester/jms-00WA</fr:addr><fr:route>foreign-forester-jms-00WA.xml</fr:route><fr:title
text="Rendering only a subset of the forest">Rendering only a subset of the forest</fr:title></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>A new option has been added to the <fr:code>forester build</fr:code> command to render only certain trees. For example, the following command will render only the trees at addresses <fr:code>xxx-MMMM</fr:code> and <fr:code>yyy-NNNN</fr:code>:</fr:p><fr:pre>forester build forest.toml --render-only=xxx-MMMM,yyy-NNNN</fr:pre><fr:p>Note that in order to maintain a correct graph analysis, the entire forest will nonetheless be <fr:em>evaluated</fr:em>. As rendering is the slowest part of the process, however, this option can still save a lot of time. In the future it could be useful to have a more sophisticated option that renders (e.g.) all children of a given tree, etc.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
show-metadata="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="foreign-forester-jonmsterling.xml"
title="Jon Sterling"
addr="//forester/jonmsterling"
type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>6</fr:month><fr:day>15</fr:day></fr:date><fr:anchor>8555</fr:anchor><fr:addr
type="user">//forester/jms-00SP</fr:addr><fr:route>foreign-forester-jms-00SP.xml</fr:route><fr:title
text="Changed behaviour of queries">Changed behaviour of queries</fr:title></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Forester’s <fr:link
href="foreign-forester-jms-0066.xml"
title="Forester 2.2 › queries"
addr="//forester/jms-0066"
type="local">rudimentary support for queries</fr:link> has been simplified somewhat. Previously, the results of a query would be gathered and, if non-empty, placed underneath an anonymous subtree (whose title could be modified using <fr:link
href="foreign-forester-jms-0067.xml"
title="Forester 2.2 › flexible transclusion options"
addr="//forester/jms-0067"
type="local">transclusion options</fr:link>).</fr:p><fr:p>In light of the <fr:link
href="foreign-forester-jms-00O4.xml"
title="Forester 3.1 › inline subtrees"
addr="//forester/jms-00O4"
type="local">user-level support for anonymous subtrees</fr:link> introduced in <fr:link
href="foreign-forester-jms-00HY.xml"
title="Forester 3.1"
addr="//forester/jms-00HY"
type="local">Forester 3.1</fr:link>, the behaviour of queries has been simplified: the results of a query are simply transcluded directly without being enclosed in a subtree.</fr:p><fr:p>Although the new behaviour is simpler, it is no longer possible to have a query subtree that is hidden when it returns no results. Users should treat the querying feature as highly provisional, and subject to change and even potential removal.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
show-metadata="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="foreign-forester-jonmsterling.xml"
title="Jon Sterling"
addr="//forester/jonmsterling"
type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>6</fr:month><fr:day>15</fr:day></fr:date><fr:anchor>8556</fr:anchor><fr:addr
type="user">//forester/jms-00SQ</fr:addr><fr:route>foreign-forester-jms-00SQ.xml</fr:route><fr:title
text="Addresses for anonymous trees">Addresses for anonymous trees</fr:title></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Previously, a subtree could be emitted without any address; this greatly complicated the logic of the graph analysis, <fr:link
href="foreign-forester-jms-00O3.xml"
title="Forester 3.1 › designated parents"
addr="//forester/jms-00O3"
type="local">designated parents</fr:link>, and other things. Now, emitting an anonymous subtree generates a fresh address in a separate namespace; as a result, these trees get rendered to their own XML file. Naturally, an anonymous subtree cannot be linked to or transcluded, but it can now participate properly in the graph analysis.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
show-metadata="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="foreign-forester-jonmsterling.xml"
title="Jon Sterling"
